# Copy to .env.local and adjust. TarifGuard is a thin read-only client over the
# deterministic TarifHub serving API. It never computes or stores a billing value.

# --- Deterministic backend (Quarkus serving service) ---
# Base URL of the serving API. Used SERVER-SIDE only (by the route handlers in
# app/api/* and lib/api.ts). It is never exposed to the browser.
#   local mvn quarkus:dev -> http://localhost:8080
#   in-cluster (Helm)     -> http://tarifhub-serving:8080
SERVING_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8080

# --- LLM routing for the /explain screen (data sovereignty) ---
# The natural-language "explain / TARMED<->TARDOC cross-walk" feature is served by
# the deterministic backend's explanation seam and routed via an EU-resident managed
# model: AWS Bedrock EU (e.g. eu-central-1) or Google Vertex AI EU. Patient
# identifiers never leave Swiss infrastructure: the app sends ONLY de-identified
# coding context, built exclusively by lib/deident.ts (see AGENTS.md rule 7).
# These are read by the backend, not by TarifGuard; listed here for operator context.
# LLM_PROVIDER=bedrock-eu            # or: vertex-eu
# LLM_REGION=eu-central-1
